<DocsLayout title="§9 Capabilities" description="RCAN §9 — Capabilities. Robots declare their capabilities in the RCAN config and mDNS TXT records. This section defines the standard capability identifiers (nav, vision, chat, teleop, arm, status), how capabilities gate scope access, and the capability negotiation handshake between client and robot.">
  <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
    <h1 class="mb-0">§9 Capabilities</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="flex gap-2 mb-8 flex-wrap">
    <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-green-500/10 text-green-400 border border-green-500/20">
      Status: Stable
    </span>
    <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-accent/10 text-accent border border-accent/20">
      RCAN v1.3
    </span>
    <a href="/spec/" class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-white/5 text-text-muted border border-white/10 hover:border-white/20">
      ← Back to Specification
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="not-prose bg-cyan-500/5 border border-cyan-500/20 rounded-xl p-6 mb-10">
    <p class="text-sm text-cyan-300/80">
      <strong class="text-cyan-400">Overview:</strong> Robots declare their capabilities in the RCAN config and mDNS TXT records. This section defines the standard capability identifiers (nav, vision, chat, teleop, arm, status), how capabilities gate scope access, and the capability negotiation handshake between client and robot.
